properties.Name: LifeInsuranceProductParticipatoryStatusType
properties.Description:
The status of whether the policy owner receives a portion of the dividable surplus of the insurance company.

Life insurance policies may be either participating or non-participating.

PARTICIPATING

The policy owner receives shares or dividends of the divided surplus of the company.

NON-PARTICIPATING

Insurance under which the insured is not eligible to share in the divided surplus of the company.

At the end of each year or annual period, the insurance company analyzes its operations and determines whether a divisible surplus has resulted - if fewer insureds have died than was estimated.   If so the company can return a part of the premiums paid for participating policies.

These payments are called dividends.    Policy dividends are not taxable income.

Properties.Description:
The status of whether the policy owner receives a portion of the dividable surplus of the insurance company.

Life insurance policies may be either participating or non-participating.

PARTICIPATING

The policy owner receives shares or dividends of the divided surplus of the company.

NON-PARTICIPATING

Insurance under which the insured is not eligible to share in the divided surplus of the company.

At the end of each year or annual period, the insurance company analyzes its operations and determines whether a divisible surplus has resulted - if fewer insureds have died than was estimated.   If so the company can return a part of the premiums paid for participating policies.

These payments are called dividends.    Policy dividends are not taxable income.
